<h3 id="getting-into-debugging">Getting into Debugging</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Python executes the statement one after other and shows the output.</li>
  <li>Shall we understand program execution? for that we need to debug</li>
  <li>We need to tell editor (IDE) from where do you want to take control of execution and in that line enable <strong>breakpoint</strong></li>
  <li>
    <p>Put the cursor the line where you want to take control from and Toggle Breakpoint
<img src="../../../../assets/python45.png" alt="preview" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>Now start debugging</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="../../../../assets/python46.png" alt="preview" />
<img src="../../../../assets/python47.png" alt="preview" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Now the program execution stops on line 1 and from there step over (Execute this line and stop and next line)</li>
</ul>

